            <h4>FhirBridge</h4>
            <p>FhirBridge is an open source experimental FHIR server built ontop of fhirbase. Fhirbase is an opensource implementation
              of the FHIR specification built entirely in Postgresql. It serves as the backend database for Fhir widget where resources
              are stored as json.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://github.com/fhirbase/fhirbase">Fhirbase</a>
            <br>
            <a class="link" href="https://github.com/NomanTrips/alpha-chase">FhirBridge source</a>           
            <h4>FHIR</h4>
            <p>FHIR, which stands for Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources is a new heatlh IT interoperability standard
              developed by HL7. The standard uses HTTP for communication with the model of RESTful web services as it's architecture, the
              same kind of technology that the rest of the civilized IT world has been using for years.</p>
